17// Accumulate the product of 2 QInt8 inputs on 32 bits to prevent
18// overflows
19template<> struct scalar_product_traits<QInt8, QInt8>
20{
21 enum {
22 Defined = 1
23 };
24 typedef QInt32 ReturnType;
25};
26
27// Accumulate the product of QInt8 inputs with QUint8 inputs on 32 bits
28// to prevent overflows
29template<> struct scalar_product_traits<QInt8, QUInt8>
30{
31 enum {
32 Defined = 1
33 };
34 typedef QInt32 ReturnType;
35};
36
37// Description of the product implementation. It's pretty simple now since
38// nothing is vectorized yet.
39// This definition tackle the case where both lhs and rhs are encoded using
40// signed 8bit integers
41#ifndef EIGEN_USE_OPTIMIZED_INT8_INT8_MAT_MAT_PRODUCT
42
43template<bool _ConjLhs, bool _ConjRhs>
44class gebp_traits<QInt8, QInt8, _ConjLhs, _ConjRhs>
45{
46public:
47 typedef QInt8 LhsScalar;
48 typedef QInt8 RhsScalar;
49 typedef QInt32 ResScalar;
50
51 enum {
52 // register block size along the M and N directions
53 // One for the current implementation
54 nr = 1,
55 mr = 1,
56 // Progress made at each iteration of the product loop
57 // also 1 for the current implementation
58 LhsProgress = 1,
59 RhsProgress = 1
60 };
61};
62
63// The signed 8bit Mat-Mat product itself.
64template<typename Index, typename DataMapper, int mr, int nr, bool ConjugateLhs, bool ConjugateRhs>
65struct gebp_kernel<QInt8, QInt8, Index, DataMapper, mr, nr, ConjugateLhs, ConjugateRhs>
66{
67 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE
68 void operator()(const DataMapper& res, const QInt8* blockA, const QInt8* blockB,
69 Index rows, Index depth, Index cols, QInt32 alpha,
70 Index strideA=-1, Index strideB=-1, Index offsetA=0, Index offsetB=0);
71};
72
73template<typename Index, typename DataMapper, int mr, int nr, bool ConjugateLhs, bool ConjugateRhs>
74EIGEN_DONT_INLINE
75void gebp_kernel<QInt8, QInt8, Index, DataMapper, mr, nr, ConjugateLhs, ConjugateRhs>
76::operator()(const DataMapper& res, const QInt8* blockA, const QInt8* blockB,
77 Index rows, Index depth, Index cols, QInt32 alpha,
78 Index strideA, Index strideB, Index offsetA, Index offsetB)
79{
80 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT(!ConjugateLhs, YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE);
81 EIGEN_STATIC_ASSERT(!ConjugateRhs, YOU_MADE_A_PROGRAMMING_MISTAKE);
82
83 eigen_assert(alpha.value == 1);
84 eigen_assert(strideA == -1);
85 eigen_assert(strideB == -1);
86 eigen_assert(offsetA == 0);
87 eigen_assert(offsetB == 0);
88
89 eigen_assert(rows > 0);
90 eigen_assert(cols > 0);
91 eigen_assert(depth > 0);
92 eigen_assert(blockA);
93 eigen_assert(blockB);
94
95 for (Index j = 0; j < cols; ++j) {
96 Index startB = j * depth;
97
98 for (Index i = 0; i < rows; ++i) {
99 Index startA = i * depth;
100
101 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; ++k) {
102 res(i, j) += blockA[startA + k] * blockB[startB + k];
103 }
104 }
105 }
106}
107#endif
108

110// This definition tackle the case where the lhs is encoded using signed 8bit
111// integers and the rhs using unsigned 8bit integers.
112#ifndef EIGEN_USE_OPTIMIZED_INT8_UINT8_MAT_MAT_PRODUCT
113template<bool _ConjLhs, bool _ConjRhs>
114class gebp_traits<QInt8, QUInt8, _ConjLhs, _ConjRhs>
115{
116public:
117 typedef QInt8 LhsScalar;
118 typedef QUInt8 RhsScalar;
119 typedef QInt32 ResScalar;
120
121 enum {
122 // register block size along the M and N directions
123 // One for the current implementation
124 nr = 1,
125 mr = 1,
126 // Progress made at each iteration of the product loop
127 // also 1 for the current implementation
128 LhsProgress = 1,
129 RhsProgress = 1
130 };
131};

133// Mat-Mat product of a signed 8bit lhs with an unsigned 8bit rhs
134template<typename Index, typename DataMapper, int mr, int nr, bool ConjugateLhs, bool ConjugateRhs>
135struct gebp_kernel<QInt8, QUInt8, Index, DataMapper, mr, nr, ConjugateLhs, ConjugateRhs>
136{
137 EIGEN_DONT_INLINE
138 void operator()(const DataMapper& res, const QInt8* blockA, const QUInt8* blockB,
139 Index rows, Index depth, Index cols, QInt32 alpha,
140 Index strideA=-1, Index strideB=-1, Index offsetA=0, Index offsetB=0);
141};

146::operator()(const DataMapper& res, const QInt8* blockA, const QUInt8* blockB,

149{

154 eigen_assert(strideA == -1);

156 eigen_assert(offsetA == 0);
157 eigen_assert(offsetB == 0);
158
159 eigen_assert(rows > 0);
160 eigen_assert(cols > 0);
161 eigen_assert(depth > 0);
162 eigen_assert(blockA);
163 eigen_assert(blockB);
164

166 Index startB = j * depth;
167
168 for (Index i = 0; i < rows; ++i) {
169 Index startA = i * depth;

171 for (Index k = 0; k < depth; ++k) {
172 res(i, j) += blockA[startA + k] * blockB[startB + k];

174 }
175 }
176}
177#endif
